   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Twenty THE BLOOD AND WATER OF THE CROSS Scripture: John 19:34-37 Men s twofold need Men have sins.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Because of this they need the forgiveness of sins.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Men also are destined to die.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>For this reason they need the eternal life, the life of God.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Elaborate more on this point.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The Lord s twofold salvation Since men have sins, the first aspect of the Lord s salvation is redemption.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Since men are destined to die, the second aspect of the Lord s salvation is to give men a life that will never die, an eternal life.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The twofold meaning of the cross The Lord s salvation is by means of the cross.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Without the cross there is no salvation.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The first aspect of the salvation of the cross is redemption, the forgiveness of men s sins.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>This is why the Lord shed His blood on the cross.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The blood is for redemption.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The blood is the price for redemption to redeem men from under the condemnation of the law.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>The blood speaks to men that the crucified Christ has already borne their sins before God.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The shedding of the blood declares that men s sins may be forgiven.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>The second aspect of the salvation of the cross is the releasing of the Lord s life.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>This is why on the cross not only blood, but also water came out from the Lord.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Originally the Lord s life was in the Lord Himself; it could not enter men to be men s life.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The death on the cross caused the Lord s body to be broken and through this, the life within Him flowed out.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>Now, men only have to receive Him to obtain His life.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>How to receive the twofold salvation of the blood and water Confess that you are sinful as well as in death.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>Believe that the Lord Jesus died and resurrected for you.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Confess that His blood has redeemed you from your sins.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Also realize that His resurrection life causes you to have God s life.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>Receive Christ as your personal Savior.</S>
   </TEXT>
